---
import LegalLayout from "../layouts/LegalLayout.astro";
import { GITHUB_URL } from "../config";
---

<LegalLayout title="Terms of Service" lastUpdated="July 20, 2026">
  <p>
    These are the terms for using LasagnaFi, a personal finance app made by
    <strong>SuperCoolLabs LLC</strong>. By using the app, you agree to them.
  </p>

  <h2>The big one: we are not a financial advisor</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>
      LasagnaFi is not a registered investment advisor, broker, or financial
      planner, and nothing in the app is financial, investment, tax, or legal
      advice.
    </strong>
    Everything you see is for information and education only. We show you your
    numbers and point out things worth thinking about, but we don't know your
    full situation and we can't make decisions for you.
  </p>
  <p>
    The insights are generated in part by AI and can be wrong or incomplete.
    Always double-check the numbers, and talk to a licensed professional before
    making any real money decision. Any action you take based on the app is your
    own choice, and you're responsible for it.
  </p>

  <h2>Using the app</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>You need to be at least 18 to use LasagnaFi.</li>
    <li>Keep your login secure, and let us know if something looks off.</li>
    <li>
      Don't misuse the service. No trying to break it, scrape it, or use it to
      harm others.
    </li>
    <li>The information you give us should be accurate and yours to share.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Connecting your accounts</h2>
  <p>
    When you link a financial account, you're letting us pull your balances and
    transactions through Plaid so the app can do its job. Connections are
    read-only, so we can see your accounts but we can never move your money. How
    we handle that data is covered in our
    <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Paid plans</h2>
  <p>
    Some features need a paid subscription. Payments are handled by Stripe. Plans
    renew automatically until you cancel, and you can cancel anytime from
    Settings. Prices may change, but we'll tell you first.
  </p>

  <h2>Your data and deleting your account</h2>
  <p>
    Your data stays yours. You can disconnect accounts or delete your account
    entirely from Settings at any time. If you'd rather keep everything on your
    own server, LasagnaFi is
    <a href={GITHUB_URL} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">open source</a>
    and you're free to self-host it.
  </p>

  <h2>No liability</h2>
  <p>
    We work hard to keep LasagnaFi accurate and available, but we provide it
    "as is" and "as available," with no warranties of any kind. We can't promise
    it will always be correct, uninterrupted, or error-free, and the information
    it shows is for information and education only, not financial advice.
  </p>
  <p>
    To the maximum extent permitted by law, SuperCoolLabs LLC is not liable for
    any damages, losses, or costs arising from your use of the app, from any
    errors or downtime, or from any decision you make in reliance on its
    information. You use LasagnaFi at your own risk.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to these terms</h2>
  <p>
    We may update these terms from time to time. When we do, we'll change the
    "Last updated" date at the top. If you keep using the app, that means you're
    okay with the new terms.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact us</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about these terms? Email us at
    <a href="mailto:support@lasagnafi.com">support@lasagnafi.com</a>.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
